=\"has-arrow\">Facebook</a></p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"cell\" data-item-id=\"51\" ng-show=\"items[51]\"><div class=\"pack-teaser\"><div class=\"pack-teaser__media\"><img class=\"js-lazyload-image\" src=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/80bA26cPQ1hEJDFjpUKntxfqdmG3ZykO/static/images/placeholder.fc1d63f8f093.gif\" data-original=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/resources/filer_thumbnails/3a/29/3a294dc3-261a-4828-9555-94f67f687173/cairo_ug_banner.png__300x300_q85_crop_subsampling-2_upscale.jpg\"></div><h2 class=\"pack-teaser__title\">Cairo</h2><div class=\"pack-teaser__description\"><div class=\"body-text body-text--small\"><p><p>This group is intended to build a stronger and bigger Ableton and Music Production community in Cairo. We will be hosting workshops and Music production related events all year long. Feel free to invite any musicians or friends that might be interested! </p></p><h3>Organizers:</h3><p>\n                \n                  Hussein Sherbini\n                \n              </p><h3>Links:</h3><p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/AbletonCairo/\" class=\"has-arrow\">Facebook</a></p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"cell\" data-item-id=\"25\" ng-show=\"items[25]\"><div class=\"pack-teaser\"><div class=\"pack-teaser__media\"><img class=\"js-lazyload-image\" src=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/80bA26cPQ1hEJDFjpUKntxfqdmG3ZykO/static/images/placeholder.fc1d63f8f093.gif\" data-original=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/resources/filer_thumbnails/unsorted-uploads/screenshot_2023-03-16_at_113925.png__300x300_q85_crop_subsampling-2_upscale.jpg\"></div><h2 class=\"pack-teaser__title\">Calgary</h2><div class=\"pack-teaser__description\"><div class=\"body-text body-text--small\"><p><p>Calgary Ableton Users Group is an Ableton approved monthly meet-up of the cities avid users. We aim to explore new techniques, expand the community and learn from one another! The event is hosted at Beat Drop on the first Friday of the month. It is a FREE event and completely open to the public. Come join us!</p></p><h3>Organizers:</h3><p>\n                \n                  Leif Olson\n                \n              </p><h3>Links:</h3><p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/calgaryabletonusergroup/\" class=\"has-arrow\">Facebook</a></p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"cell\" data-item-id=\"174\" ng-show=\"items[174]\"><div class=\"pack-teaser\"><div class=\"pack-teaser__media\"><img class=\"js-lazyload-image\" src=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/80bA26cPQ1hEJDFjpUKntxfqdmG3ZykO/static/images/placeholder.fc1d63f8f093.gif\" data-original=\"https://cdn-resources.ableton.com/resources/filer_thumbnails/images/user-groups/cape_town_ug_fb_banner3.png__300x300_q85_crop_subsampling-2_upscale.jpg\"></div><h2 class=\"pack-teaser__title\">Cape Town</h2><div class=\"pack-teaser__description\"><div class=\"body-text body-text--small\"><p><p>The Ableton User Group, Cape Town is a forum for users and lovers of Ableton Live software from all skill levels; no matter if you\'re just getting started or are a long time Ableton veteran, you are welcome. On the web, the Facebook Group serves as both a community discussion place and a notice board for any events and other exciting happenings! In the real world FREE events of all shapes and sizes are held semi-regularly and include discussions, demos and performances from some big local names - all focused on the use (and sometimes misuse) of Ableton Live. These events are completely free and open to the public! The events also serve to build a community of Live users in Cape Town so that new users might meet experienced users who can give them a hand and experienced users can meet other experienced users and bounce ideas and form collaborations.</p><p></p><p>Please join the mailing list to get notified of future events: http://eepurl.com/byxNBD</p></p><h3>Organizers:</h3><p>\n                \n                  William Glendinning\n                \n              <